      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TERRA MAY (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing seventh (31.05) in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park. Has a good record here including two wins. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and is a key runner. TURN UP ACE (3) steps out a further 83m to an untried trip. Comes here a last start placegetter at Wentworth Park in Grade 5 (30.36). With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. RAINBOW SHOUT (8) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing fourth (35.70) at The Gardens in a Grade 5. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw. Rates a winning chance on best. LIGHTNING LOTTE (5) cannot be dismissed although new to this distance.",
